race_name: VFW Sport Clips Help A Hero 200
race_comments: Elliott Sadler won the VFW Sport Clips Help a Hero 200 at Darlington Raceway, his 12th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory.

Austin Dillon won the Food City 300 at Bristol Motor Speedway, his eighth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: #7 and 18 (unapproved adjusments) and #10 (missing the drivers meeting).

Erik Jones won the Fitzgerald Glider Kits 300 at Bristol Motor Speedway, his third NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, no cars 
dropped to the rear of the field.

Dale Earnhardt Jr. won the ToyotaCare 250 at Richmond International Raceway, his 24th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field: No. 43 (engine change).

Kyle Busch won the Virginia529 College Savings 250 at Richmond International Raceway, his 84th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: #25 (driver change).

race_name: Road America 180 Fired Up by Johnsonville
race_comments: Michael McDowell won the Road America 180 Fired Up by Johnsonville at Road America, his first NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: Nos. 88, 89, 39, 0, 77, 97, 13, 74 (unapproved adjustments) and No. 40 (missing driver introductions).
Austin Dillon won the TreatMyClot.com 300 by Janssen at Auto Club Speedway, his 7th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Erik Jones won the Drive For Safety 300 at Chicagoland Speedway, his sixth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: Nos. 33, 40 and 77 (unapproved adjustments).

Daniel Suarez won the Ford EcoBoost 300 at Homestead-Miami Speedway, his third career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field under penalty.

Kyle Busch won the Kansas Lottery 300 at Kansas Speedway, his 85th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: Nos. 48, 42 and 93 (unapproved adjustments).

Kyle Busch won the Boyd Gaming 300 at Las Vegas Motor Speedway, his 78th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the 

race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field: No. 15 (driver change) and No. 44 (unapproved adjustments).
Kyle Busch won the O'Reilly Auto Parts 300 at Texas Motor Speedway, his 80th NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Kyle Larson won the O'Reilly Auto Parts Challenge, his fifth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 07 (unapproved adjustments).

Elliott Sadler won the VisitMyrtleBeach.com 300, his 13th NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 13 (driver change).

Kyle Busch won the Alsco 300 at Kentucky Speedway, his 81st career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 3 and 13 (unapproved adjustments).

Justin Marks won the Mid-Ohio Challenge at Mid-Ohio Sports Car Course, his 1st NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 0, 3, 07, 22, 78, 93 (unapproved adjustments).

Elliott Sadler won the Sparks Energy 300 at Talladega Superspeedway, his 11th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 88 (missing driver intros), No. 85 (missing drivers meeting).

Kyle Busch won the AXALTA Faster. Tougher. Brighter. 200 at Phoenix International Raceway, his 79th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field: Nos. 28 and 78 (unapproved adjustment); No. 15 (backup car and driver change).

Kyle Busch won the Ticket Galaxy 200 at Phoenix International Raceway, his 86th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 22 and 24 (unapproved adjustments).

Daniel Suarez won the Drive Sober 200 at Dover International Speedway, his second career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: Nos. 15, 3 (unapproved adjustments) and Nos. 2, 18, 22 (driver change).
Erik Jones won the Ollie's Bargain Outlet 200 at Dover International Speedway, his fourth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. No cars started the race from the rear of the field.

Aric Almirola won the Subway Firecracker 250 Powered by Coca-Cola, his second NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the folllowing cars dropped to the rear of the field: #78 (unapproved adjustments).
Chase Elliott won the Powershare QQQ 300 at Daytona International Speedway, his fifth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Kyle Busch won the Heads Up Georgia 250 at Atlanta Motor Speedway, his 77th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the 
following car dropped to the rear of the field: No. 25 (unapproved adjustments).
Kyle Busch won the Lilly Diabetes 250 at Indianapolis Motor Speedway, his 83rd career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory.

Daniel Suarez won the Menards 250 presented by Valvoline at Michigan International Speedway, his first NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Kyle Busch won the AutoLotto 200 at New Hampshire Motor Speedway, his 82nd career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 07, 44 and 89 (unapproved adjustments), No. 14 (engine change).

Joey Logano won the Zippo 200 at Watkins Glen International, his 26th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 01, 14, 16, 25, 28, 40, 74, 77 (Unapproved adjustments).

race_name: Blue Cross Blue Shield of North Carolina Drive for the Cure 300
race_comments: Joey Logano won the Drive for the Cure 300 at Charlotte Motor Speedway, his 27th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: Nos. 13, 40 and 74 (missed drivers meeting).

Denny Hamlin won the Hisense 4K TV 300 at Charlotte Motor Speedway, his 15th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 25 and No. 43 (unapproved adjustments).

Kyle Larson won the Pocono Green 250 at Pocono Raceway, his fourth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: Nos. 14, 74 (unapproved adjustments).

race_name: American Ethanol E15 250 presented by Enogen
race_comments: Sam Hornish Jr. won the American Ethanol E15 250 Presented by Enogen at Iowa Speedway, his fourth NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: Nos. 1, 20, 22 (unapproved body modifications); Nos. 4, 62 (unapproved adjustments).
Erik Jones won the U.S. Cellular 250 at Iowa Speedway, his fifth NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the No. 52 dropped to the rear of the field for unapproved adjustments.
